    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to Learn Rugby, your comprehensive guide to learning and mastering the game of rugby. Whether you're a beginner or an intermediate player, this website will provide you with valuable information, tips, and drills to enhance your skills and understanding of the game.</p>
    
    <h2>Basic Rules</h2>
    <p>Before diving into the specifics of playing rugby, it's important to familiarize yourself with the basic rules of the game:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Rugby is played with two teams, each consisting of 15 players.</li>
      <li>The objective is to score points by carrying, passing, or kicking the ball to the opposing team's goal area and touching it down.</li>
      <li>Forward passes are not allowed; the ball must be passed backward or kicked forward.</li>
      <li>Tackling is a key element of the game, where players can bring down the ball carrier to regain possession.</li>
      <li>Scoring can be achieved through tries (touching the ball down in the goal area), conversions, penalties, or drop goals.</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>Skills and Techniques</h2>
    <p>To become a proficient rugby player, it's important to develop various skills and techniques. Here are some key areas to focus on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Passing and catching</li>
      <li>Tackling and defense</li>
      <li>Running with the ball</li>
      <li>Kicking and field positioning</li>
      <li>Rucking and mauling</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Training Drills</h2>
    <p>Practice makes perfect! Here are a few training drills that can help you improve your rugby skills:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Passing and receiving drills</li>
      <li>Tackling technique drills</li>
      <li>Agility and footwork exercises</li>
      <li>Kicking and catching drills</li>
      <li>Game simulation drills</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>Resources</h2>
    <p>For further learning and reference, here are some recommended resources:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Books and instructional videos</li>
      <li>Online tutorials and courses</li>
      <li>Local rugby clubs and coaches</li>
   

